{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc27426ee-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s112"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"112"},"text":"§ 112.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Presidential memorial certificate program","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc27426ef-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s112/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" At the request of the President the Secretary may conduct a program for honoring the memory of deceased persons eligible for burial in a national cemetery by reason of any of paragraphs (1), (2), (3), or (7) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s2402/a"},"text":"section 2402(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":", by preparing and sending to eligible recipients a certificate bearing the signature of the President and expressing the country’s grateful recognition of the deceased individual’s service in the Armed Forces. The award of a certificate to one eligible recipient will not preclude authorization of another certificate if a request is received from some other eligible recipient."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc27426f0-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s112/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For the purpose of this section an “eligible recipient” means the next of kin, a relative or friend upon request, or an authorized service representative acting on behalf of such relative or friend.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc27426f1-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s112/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A certificate may not be furnished under the program under subsection (a) on behalf of a deceased person described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s2411/b"},"text":"section 2411(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc27426f2-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/88/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–88, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-07-24"},"text":"July 24, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/264"},"text":"79 Stat. 264","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s4/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 4(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(E), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/404"},"text":"105 Stat. 404","children":[],"tail":", 405; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/330/tII/s201/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–330, title II, § 201(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-06"},"text":"Dec. 6, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2823"},"text":"116 Stat. 2823","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/154/tVI/s603"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–154, title VI, § 603","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1201"},"text":"126 Stat. 1201","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/315/tIII/s302/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–315, title III, § 302(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/1551"},"text":"130 Stat. 1551","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc27426f3-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc27426f4-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc27426f5-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/315"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–315","children":[],"tail":" substituted “persons eligible for burial in a national cemetery by reason of any of paragraphs (1), (2), (3), or (7) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s2402/a"},"text":"section 2402(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":",” for “veterans, discharged under honorable conditions, and persons who died in the active military, naval, or air service,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/154"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–154","children":[],"tail":" inserted “and persons who died in the active military, naval, or air service,” after “under honorable conditions,” and substituted “deceased individual’s” for “veteran’s”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/330"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–330","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc27426f6-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc27426f7-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2016 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/315/tIII/s302/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–315, title III, § 302(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/1551"},"text":"130 Stat. 1551","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/114/315/tIII/s302/b"},"text":"“The amendment made by subsection (a) [amending this section] shall apply with respect to the death of a person eligible for burial in a national cemetery by reason of paragraph (1), (2), (3), or (7) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s2402/a"},"text":"section 2402(a) of title 38","children":[],"tail":", United States Code, occurring before, on, or after the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2016","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc27426f8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2002 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/330/tII/s201/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–330, title II, § 201(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-06"},"text":"Dec. 6, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2823"},"text":"116 Stat. 2823","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/107/330/tII/s201/d"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section and sections 2301 and 2306 of this title] shall apply with respect to deaths occurring on or after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-06"},"text":"Dec. 6, 2002","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
